{"key":"processedPost-8730730","value":{"id":8730730,"first":8719223,"last":8731256,"when":1217986175,"utime":"08/06/08 04:29 AM","content":"My experience is that it's far easier to maintain high humidity with proper air exchange by placing the unit inside the greenhouse, and then cutting windows and slits for FAE.&nbsp; The windows ensure that the interior never gets stale, and the coolmist recycling humid air increases humidity over the one-pass method you get when piping it in.&nbsp;  In addition, adding hoses and/or blocking the natural output causes static pressure which ruins the bushings sooner, resulting in motor failure as it loads down.<br /><br />It took a few years and a huge pile of wasted vics humidifiers to learn that lesson.&nbsp; With the unit inside the greenhouse, it will last much longer.&nbsp; Use a timer and dial it in so you get maximum humidity with as little water on the sides and floor as possible.<br />RR","title":"Re: advice on installing cool mist setup in a martha (hoses)"}}